elements.title: Marvin Harrison Jr.
elements.contents: ... that one NFL scout compared watching Marvin Harrison Jr. (pictured) to "window shopping at a Lamborghini dealership for the model that doesn't come out until next year"?

elements.title: Locumba uprising
elements.contents: ...that the Locumba uprising was thought by many to be a cover for the escape of Vladimiro Montesinos, Peru's de facto leader from 1990 to 2000?

elements.title: Edward D. Boone
elements.contents: ... that Edward D. Boone was the last surviving member of his 1851 graduating class from the College of the Holy Cross?

elements.title: Surrexit a mortuis
elements.contents: ... that the Easter composition Surrexit a mortuis ('He rose from the dead') was scored for choir and two organs by Charles-Marie Widor, the organist at Saint-Sulpice in Paris?

elements.title: William L. Breckinridge
elements.contents: ... that one abolitionist said that William L. Breckinridge's anti-slavery views would "disqualify [him] from political usefulness"?

elements.title: ius civile vigilantibus scriptum est
elements.contents: ... that variations of the Latin legal maxim ius civile vigilantibus scriptum est have been used by American, European and Lesotho courts?

elements.title: Standseilbahn Linth-Limmern
elements.contents: ... that the Standseilbahn Linth-Limmern, the funicular railway with the highest transport payload capacity (215 tonnes), was built to move four transformers 882 m (2,894 ft) uphill?

elements.title: Bettina Petzold-Mähr
elements.contents: ... that before becoming a legislator, Bettina Petzold-Mähr played volleyball for Liechtenstein when they defeated Lichtenstein?
